{
  "page": "Defender of the Dispossessed",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Defender of the Dispossessed</b> is an honorary title claimed by the Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Manderly\" title=\"House Manderly\">House Manderly</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/White_Harbor\" title=\"White Harbor\">White Harbor</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> It most likely relates to the Manderlys' status as refugees from the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a>, from where <a href=\"/index.php/House_Gardener\" title=\"House Gardener\">House Gardener</a> sent them into exile in the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a> (where they were welcomed by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">House Stark</a>), and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Peake\" title=\"House Peake\">House Peake</a> occupied their castle <a href=\"/index.php/Dunstonbury\" title=\"Dunstonbury\">Dunstonbury</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_north.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_north.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_Defenders_of_the_Dispossessed\">Known Defenders of the Dispossessed</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Defender_of_the_Dispossessed&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known Defenders of the Dispossessed\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Wyman_Manderly\" title=\"Wyman Manderly\">Wyman Manderly</a>, Lord of White Harbor, is the current Defender of the Dispossessed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Defender_of_the_Dispossessed&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: See also\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Marshal_of_the_Mander\" title=\"Lord Marshal of the Mander\">Lord Marshal of the Mander</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Shield_of_the_Faith\" title=\"Shield of the Faith\">Shield of the Faith</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Warden_of_the_White_Knife\" title=\"Warden of the White Knife\">Warden of the White Knife</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_White_Harbor\" title=\"Lord of White Harbor\">Lord of White Harbor</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Defender_of_the_Dispossessed&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_19\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 19\">Chapter 19</a>, Davos III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_north.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_north.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, the North.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403163239\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.012 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.012 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 231/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8492/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 846/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 112/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 8/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1285/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    6.410      1 -total\n 98.06%    6.286      3 Template:Ref\n 61.21%    3.924      3 Template:Ref/core\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:20850-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403163239 and revision id 211910\n -->\n",
